###########################################################################
#  text_smcp_kerned_lig - smcp synthesis interacting with the AFM kern    #
#  pair matrix and the OpenType ligature allowlist in a single run.        #
#                                                                          #
#  text_smcp_active pins smcp / onum glyph substitution in isolation;      #
#  text_ligatures_kerned pins ligatures+kerning in isolation.  This        #
#  snippet wires both gates on at once so that any regression in the       #
#  ordering of kerning -> ligature folding -> smcp glyph rewrite in        #
#  z53.c's font pipeline (svg_font_apply_features /                        #
#  svg_font_has_ligatures / svg_font_kerning_pair) shows up as a pixel     #
#  divergence here even when the simpler companions still pass.            #
#                                                                          #
#  Independent verification: run_compare.sh routes this snippet through   #
#  the same LOUT_SVG_FONT_FEATURES env-var trigger as text_smcp_active   #
#  so the SVG output should contain at least one "<path d=" emission       #
#  for the smcp-rewritten words.                                           #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
AVAILABLE final affinity -- one paragraph carrying an "AV" kern pair,
an "fi" ligature in "final" and an "ffi" ligature in "affinity",
followed by the words intended for smcp glyph rewrite.  WaVe ToTal
provides two more kern pairs alongside.
@End @Text
